radiographic_examinations.findings: In the right lower quadrant, subtle stranding, hyperemia and enlargement of the appendix measuring up to 10 mm. The bases of the lungs are clear without evidence of consolidation or edema. Normal liver with small hypodensities, layering small hyperdense stones in the gallbladder, unremarkable spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys. No evidence of inflammatory changes or obstruction; no free air or fluid in the abdomen.
